race.comment: ILOVETHISTOWN (2) resumes and has his first run for the Adam Trinder barn. His Victorian form reads well for this and it's a question of readiness. Won a recent synthetic trial comfortably, and he has placed first-up. Byrne Burke sticks from the trial. MONCLERE (3) is on a quick back-up and is busting to win. Missed a whisker this trip at Hobart last time and maps for the run of the race. A live chance. BELLA CHINKARA (9) resumes and will be fitter for her recent trial win here. Has a tricky gate but she has the ability and the betting will be key. Should be involved in the finish, regardless. LITTLEMISSALLSORTS (11) is a filly by Prague out of Filters on debut. Has shown enough at the trials to keep onside and apprentice Jabez Johnstone sticks from those.
